text: Not to be a spoil-sport but I really hope they don't follow the whole near-eradication-of-the-human-race plot like in the originals. I would like to see a world where there were humans that rejected their kind's need for dominance, and worked to live together for the benefit of each other (I know, this isn't Disney but still...). Caesar continues to show mercy, and a clip of both races fighting together and that little girl seemingly under their protection may show that it isn't an all-out war. I'll be glad if that's the case. I'm sure some apes would want all mankind wiped out as well, and the maneuvering in politics by both surviving races would be much more entertaining to me. But that's just me. This trailer gives nothing away besides bits to get excited about and to speculate on. I cannot wait for this movie. Loved Rise so much because of Caesar's development and Dawn for his growth as a leader. I'm so damn excited for this one!

Planet of the Apes, when it was first made back in the '60s I think, really was one of the defining moments in film history. That thought made a lot of people uncomfortable. The films that followed really have got better and better as far as I am concerned.

text: Guys I saw the video tonight and I'm gonna write some pros and cons because I don't want this text to be too long.   Pros: Long( 2 h 20 minutes) just what I like.   The film was very emotional and the message was very strong in the film.   The story was quite good and it was was easy to follow through the end.   Cool movie with all these effects and to see from the monkeys perspective, I now feel more love towards monkeys.      Cons: Some scenes were so boring because they didn't do anything  (only cry for like an whole minute or just stare at each other and say some words)  Some moves in the film were so silly and I can't quite understand why the directors actually wanted this in the movie.   There weren't many gun fights and "war things" like I expected it to be it was more like the monkeys were held in hostage and had to work for their lives.   Overall the movie was good and I watched it in 3D.  My overall rating of the movie would be 7, 5/10üòÄ
